      <hedline>
        <hl1>'Todd' in Finnish</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>James Luce letter on Stephen Sondheim and Ned Rorem's April 30 discussion on difference between opera and musicals recalls seeing Finnish National Opera production of Sweeney Todd in Helsinki (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The discussion of musicals and operas reminds me that last season I had the good luck to attend the Finnish National Opera production of ''Sweeney Todd'' in Helsinki.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The discussion of musicals and operas reminds me that last season I had the good luck to attend the Finnish National Opera production of ''Sweeney Todd'' in Helsinki.</p>
        <p>I was quite sure that what I was hearing and seeing was opera, but was that because I was in an opera house or because the performance was in a language that I scarcely understand (Finnish, with English surtitles)?</p>
        <p>JAMES LUCE  Warwick, N.Y.</p>
        <p>OPERA OR MUSICAL</p>
      </block>
